latestPosts.caption:
Where fashion editors shop: Couldn’t be close to a @thebicestercollection destination and not visit. Made a little day trip to @lasrozasvillage on a recent trip to Madrid, a quick drive from the city centre. Come for the shopping, stay for the cafés, the crisp Spanish light, and that satisfying feeling of finding the one — whether it’s the perfect pair of black heels or a forever bag you didn’t know you needed. An easy, charming day trip that feels like a well-edited escape.

🛍️Book your spot at their super chic lounge, The Apartment. Bonus? A personal shopper and hands-free shopping
🛍️ Sign up ahead of your visit for member benefits and savings
🛍️Don’t forget to ask for VAT refund. Indians can expect to get back around 15–17% of your purchase price
Happy Shopping!

latestPosts.caption: Forget labubus. I only ever want to be a Poo super fan. A fun little backstory about this story… It was at an editor’s high tea at @manishmalhotra05 Dubai store this February that I let slip my special talent: being able to seamlessly fit an iconic Poo dialogue (@kareenakapoorkhan) into any situation (try me!). @rochellepinto was so amused by my gift that when @vogueindia decided to spotlight this pop culture icon (24 years and still going strong) in their ‘Nostalgia’ issue, she asked if I’d be down to take a trip down memory lane. All I could think was “Hallelujah!”. So here we are. Much fun writing this one, in the latest issue of Vogue ♥️♥️♥️ With hot takes by @manishmalhotra05 @divyakdsouza @jibraan.khan

latestPosts.caption:
The Ease of Intention with Praachi Raniwala, Little Things edition. 

In conversation with @praachiraniwala on finding pockets of stillness amidst the bustle, quiet luxury, and living stylishly on her terms. 

As a fashion and lifestyle journalist, brand consultant, and co-founder of a floral venture, Praachi Raniwala wears many hats effortlessly. Yet behind this ease lies a deep commitment to thoughtful living and prioritising what truly matters. Dive into her afternoon at The Kin Hotel, exploring the art of self-reflection, sartorial authenticity, and navigating Bombay’s intemperate summer.

Praachi is seen wearing the Serene Forest Linen Dress and the Glimmer of Joy Tier Dress.

Photographs: Keegan Crasto (@keegancrasto @publicbutterindia)
Curation and copy: Gariyashi Bhuyan (@gariyashi_bh)
Location: The Kin, Mumbai (@thekinhotel)
